The `Sequelize.fn` method is used to apply the `COUNT` aggregation function to the `*` wildcard column, resulting in the count of rows per `validationId`. We assign an alias `'count'` to the aggregated column for better access to the count value.

Finally, we include the `group` property as an array containing the `'validationId'` string to group the results by `validationId`.

